{
  "stem": "7094.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "He wanted to keep up the religious attitudes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "As he didn't have sons, he concentrated on us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I used to go to a Jew school, which was called Bais Yaakov.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was after ordinary school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We used to go to school from 8:00 to 1:00, and then we had the Jewish Bais Yaakov from 2:00 to 5:00 every day.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was the one who originated, because he was very appalled that his daughter didn't speak Yiddish, because we spoke already Polish at home.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he realized that education is important.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he went to Krakow, which was the center of Bais Yaakov, and he brought the teacher, who lived originally with us, but later when it was organized, in a school form and he was to attend it.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had two younger sisters.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was the older one.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So life was relatively comfortable.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was very warm.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The environment was not very nice, because Poland was very anti-Semitic, and therefore the family warmth was to-- to put us-- to make us comfortable, to comfort us against-- I remember my father was-- my grandfather was bitten by a dog, you know, because as a Jew.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "During the sort of Catholic holidays, we would be afraid to go on the street, because there was quite a lot of violence too.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So outside, the world was tough, and anti-Semitism was there on every step.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But inside the family was very warm and comforting and very close.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When you said you lived in a shtetl, were you in a-- mainly amongst Jewish people in the area of the town where you lived?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was thinking about the composition of the population.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
